1) cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and argumentation mining. 
2) cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a neural network-based approach for argumentation mining. 
3) cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses a recurrent neural network architecture for the proposed joint model. 
4) cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with extracting links between argument components, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval. 
5) cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the hierarchical structure of argument components and proposes a model that enforces certain properties of the tree structure.
